It seems that with Santa having to travel at 145th. the speed of light to get all the presents to all the houses within 48hrs. (Yes, he uses the international date line to his advantage) He likes to things a little slowly while at home with Mrs. Claus.<br>
<br>
Also, after having to do all THAT in one night, he can get pretty crankey during the year if he has to do much else than eat cookies and rest.<br>
<br>
The first Christmas, Mrs. Claus said &quot;Wouldn't it be nice to have a small tree in here to decorate and gaze at&quot;<br>
<br>
Not being one to argue with Mrs. Claus and her dumb ideas, Santa figured he'd get her a tree, and headed out the door with an axe.<br>
<br>
&quot;Take an angel with you Dear, he can help you&quot; and she smiled at him as he left the house.<br>
<br>
Santa walked outside and spied a nice tree about a hundred yards away. Just as he was about to take the first swing he heard a small voice...&quot;She won't like that one, there's a nicer one over here&quot; from the angel at his side.<br>
<br>
Santa followed the angel over the hill toward the perfect tree.<br>
Everytime Santa saw a nice tree and was about to stop the Angel would say &quot;Not that one Santa, just a little further, she'll really like this one.&quot; So on he trudged through the blistering cold snowey night.<br>
<br>
Finally, half exhausted, Santa finally heard &quot;This tree Santa, this is the one.&quot; And he began to chop. The Angel of course helped by telling him to cut on a slant, and of course sang a beat to chop to. &quot;Now cut on the other side Santa&quot;, &quot;Try to do it neatly Santa&quot; &quot;She'll like this one Santa&quot;<br>
<br>
Finally the tree was down, and Santa began to drag it back to the house when the Angel said &quot;Carry it Santa, so you don't lose the needles&quot;<br>
<br>
Santa carried it. Sweat freezing on his brow.<br>
Santa got it home. There were no cookies waiting for him.<br>
Santa set it up. &quot;That's crooked santa, a little to the left&quot; the Angel piped.<br>
Santa began to decorate. &quot;No Santa, the large items belong on the bottom, it'll look prettier that way&quot;<br>
<br>
Finally, Santa had had enough &quot;HELP&quot; and said...&quot;Angel, if you say one more word, I'm going to stick this tree up your arse!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Angel said &quot;But Santa!&quot;<br>
<br>
And that's how the first Angel got atop the first Christmas tree. <p>Hanzil Sowwhat <BR>
